</taxonomicName>
is a rare species in collections, so far known only by the female form and by the 
<typeStatus id="54AB7B9AC13AA30BA649FB3072C1FDC2" box="[1388,1436,1201,1225]" pageId="9" pageNumber="549">type</typeStatus>
specimen. The wing pattern is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C10BEBBC13AA30BA145FB54742BFDE6" authority="Druce, 1910" authorityName="Druce" authorityYear="1910" box="[608,886,1237,1261]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Dysschema" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="549" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="imitata">
<emphasis id="B964192AC13AA30BA145FB54758CFDE7" box="[608,721,1237,1260]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="549">D. imitata</emphasis>
(Druce, 
<number id="3DD8D71FC13AA30BA011FB547430FDE6" box="[820,877,1237,1261]" pageId="9" pageNumber="549" value="1910.0">1910</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C10BEBBC13AA30BA089FB5473F4FDE6" authority="Druce, 1910" authorityName="Druce" authorityYear="1910" box="[940,1193,1237,1261]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Dysschema" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="549" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="titan">
<emphasis id="B964192AC13AA30BA089FB54735FFDE7" box="[940,1026,1237,1260]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="549">D. titan</emphasis>
(Druce, 
<number id="3DD8D71FC13AA30BA741FB5473FCFDE6" box="[1124,1185,1237,1261]" pageId="9" pageNumber="549" value="1910.0">1910</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
